the%20same%20friends%2C%20and%20up%20until%20school%2C%20did%20everything%20together%2C%20seven%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20the%20time%20came%20to%20apply%20for%20schools%20and%20to%20make%20the%20big%20decision%20about%20whether%20to%20continue%20this%20togetherness%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwins-were-separate-classes-school-recall-how-silly-it-was-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20separate%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20their%20lives%20by%20putting%20them%20in%20separate%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%20the%20final%20decision%20when%20we%20were%20having%20lunch%20as%20a%20family%20one%20day.%20We%20were%20practicing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhard-viral-math-questions-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimple%20math%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20boys%20kept%20answering%20for%20his%20twin%20brother.%20It's%20completely%20normal%20for%20one%20twin%20to%20be%20more%20dominant%20and%20competitive%2C%20and%20this%20wasn't%20the%20first%20time%20we'd%20seen%20this%20happen.%20But%20this%20moment%20felt%20like%20the%20last%20piece%20of%20evidence%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20needed%20to%20confirm%20that%20putting%20the%20boys%20in%20different%20classes%20at%20school%20would%20be%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20them%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOne%20twin%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20away%20from%20his%20brother%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-step-method-making-high-stakes-high-quality-decisions-fast-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaking%20this%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20like%20a%20huge%20weight%20off%20our%20minds.%20As%20well%20as%20coping%20with%20our%20own%20conflicting%20feelings%2C%20we'd%20also%20had%20many%20people%20asking%20what%20%26quot%3Bour%20plan%20for%20the%20twins%26quot%3B%20was%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20good%20to%20finally%20have%20a%20concrete%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20the%20decision%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-america-school-classes-then-and-now-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20classes%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20been%20made%20harder%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20when%20we%20asked%20the%20kids%20what%20they'd%20prefer%2C%20one%20said%20he'd%20like%20to%20be%20with%20his%20brother%2C%20while%20the%20other%20said%20he%20didn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20this%20was%20predictable%20given%20they%20have%20opposing%20opinions%20on%20most%20things%20in%20life%20at%20the%20moment.%20But%20it%20was%20also%20quite%20a%20difficult%20conversation%20to%20have%20with%20them%20because%20we%20were%20already%2099%25%20sure%20they%20would%20be%20going%20into%20separate%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20was%20posed%20in%20a%20wider%20conversation%20about%20starting%20school%2C%20what%20it%20would%20be%20like%20and%20who%20would%20be%20with%20them.%20We%20already%20knew%20the%20answer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrities-who-had-twins-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeach%20twin%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20give%2C%20and%20as%20we%20expected%2C%20the%20twin%20who%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20the%20same%20class%20as%20his%20brother%20is%20the%20one%20who%20can't%20get%20a%20word%20in%20edgeways%20sometimes.%20But%20he%20needs%20his%20own%20space%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20got%20support%20from%20everyone%20around%20us%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELife%20as%20twin%20parents%20can%20be%20exhausting%20and%20frustrating.%20Someone%20always%20needs%20something%2C%20is%20asking%20us%20questions%20or%20wants%20a%20snack.%20But%2C%20while%20it%20can%20sometimes%20be%20overwhelming%20for%20us%2C%20it%20must%20also%20feel%20intense%20for%20the%20boys%20themselves.%20While%20they%20don't%20often%20verbalize%20it%2C%20I%20think%20sometimes%20they%20must%20really%20crave%20solo%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20our%20friends%20and%20family%20agreed%20that%20separating%20the%20boys%20sounded%20like%20the%20right%20decision%2C%20which%20was%20reassuring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hate%20it%20when%20people%20ask%20if%20we're%20%26quot%3Bsplitting%20them%20up%26quot%3B%20though.%20It%20makes%20it%20sound%20like%20we're%20ending%20a%20relationship%20and%20forcing%20them%20apart.%20We%20have%20their%20best%20interests%20at%20heart%20and%20want%20them%20to%20be%20happy%20and%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20twins%20are%20non-identical%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20so%20they're%20just%20brothers%20born%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20one%20minute%20apart.%20Like%20all%20siblings%2C%20they%20have%20very%20different%20personalities%2C%20interests%2C%20and%20strengths.%20So%20far%2C%20school%20has%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20great%20place%20for%20them%20to%20develop%20these%20without%20being%20compared%20to%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20they%20have%20a%20term%20of%20school%20under%20their%20belts%2C%20we%20do%20no%20doubt%20that%20this%20was%20the%20right%20decision%20for%20our%20boys.%20They're%20creating%20bonds%20with%20their%20teachers%20and%20peers%20and%20gaining%20more%20independence%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20positive%20we've%20seen%20is%20how%20strong%20the%20bond%20between%20them%20has%20become.%20I've%20never%20seen%20them%20hug%20each%20other%20so%20much%2C%20and%20I%20love%20eavesdropping%20on%20their%20chats%20about%20what%20they've%20done%20that%20day.%20I%20know%20there%20will%20be%20challenges%20along%20the%20way%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20reassured%20that%20we've%20got%20their%20school%20days%20off%20to%20the%20best%20start%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwins-in-separate-class-school-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706966161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ba55de43bb77284b