contributed%20to%20the%20breakup%20of%20my%20marriage.%20I%20expected%20my%20ex-husband%20to%20heal%20me%20from%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fgenerational-trauma%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Echildhood%20traumas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20be%20the%20antidote%20to%20my%20bouts%20of%20depression%2C%20and%20make%20up%20for%20all%20the%20ways%20others%20let%20me%20down.%20I%20burdened%20him%20with%20an%20impossible%20task%20%E2%80%94%20to%20make%20me%20happy.%20I%20couldn't%20see%20it%20then%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20my%20husband%20to%20do%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20do%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20I%20have%20to%20work%20through%20every%20single%20issue%20in%20my%20life%20to%20find%20a%20serious%20partner%20and%20be%20married%20again%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20wrong%20to%20expect%20your%20significant%20other%20to%20provide%20some%20of%20the%20joy%20in%20your%20life.%20However%2C%20I%20now%20know%20it%20can't%20be%20my%20husband's%20job%20to%20save%20me%20from%20myself%20or%20be%20the%20source%20of%20all%20my%20happiness.%20I%20have%20to%20bring%20the%20best%20version%20of%20myself%20into%20a%20marriage%20while%20owning%20and%20actively%20managing%20the%20baggage%20I%20bring%20into%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20know%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarriage-advice-science-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emarriage%20is%20about%20commitment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20patience%2C%20and%20compromise.%20It's%20ordering%20sushi%20sometimes%20when%20what%20you%20really%20want%20is%20pizza.%20It's%20having%20uncomfortable%20conversations%20about%20money%20and%20sex%20and%20counting%20to%2010%20instead%20of%20saying%20something%20you%20can't%20take%20back.%20It's%20a%20shared%20vision%20for%20the%20future%20you%20inch%20toward%20together%20through%20mundane%20day-to-day%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20also%20learn%20a%20lot%20from%20watching%20the%20successful%20relationships%20of%20my%20loved%20ones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandparents%20were%20married%20for%2072%20years%2C%20raised%20six%20children%20in%20a%20house%20with%20one%20bathroom%2C%20and%20built%20a%20thriving%20business%20that%20employs%20much%20of%20my%20extended%20family%20today.%20That%20is%20also%20marriage%2C%20at%20its%20very%20best%20%E2%80%94%20an%20awe-inspiring%20testament%20to%20the%20power%20of%20two%20people%20who%20commit%20to%20each%20other%20to%20build%20something%20greater%20than%20themselves.%20I%20can't%20think%20of%20anything%20more%20meaningful%20and%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-youre-in-a-strong-relationship-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esuccessful%20marriages%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20my%20friends%20and%20family%20has%20been%20invaluable.%20I've%20seen%20them%20overcome%20tremendous%20obstacles%20and%20grow%20closer%20over%20circumstances%20that%20would%20have%20torn%20less%20committed%20couples%20apart.%20I've%20seen%20them%20choose%20each%20other%20day%20after%20day%20when%20it%20wasn't%20easy%20to%20do%2C%20and%20I've%20seen%20them%20set%20aside%20their%20wants%20and%20needs%20for%20their%20partner.%20I%20see%20the%20beauty%20in%20their%20devotion%20during%20a%20time%20when%20society%20puts%20freedom%20on%20a%20pedestal%20and%20applauds%20self-serving%20lifestyles.%20I%20know%20I've%20lived%20that%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20have%20some%20fears%20about%20being%20in%20a%20serious%20relationship%20and%20getting%20married%20again%20someday.%20It's%20one%20thing%20to%20better%20understand%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20a%20marriage%20last%2C%20and%20it%20is%20quite%20another%20to%20put%20it%20into%20action.%20It's%20been%20nearly%2010%20years%20since%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-nesting-divorce-parenting-plan-2023-12%5C%22%20target