20steps%2C%20he%20had%20the%20option%20to%20go%20further%20or%20to%20quit%20and%20receive%20a%20payout.%20But%20he's%20very%20dedicated.%20He%20throws%20a%20lot%20of%20himself%20into%20his%20job.%20So%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I%20can%20try%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20extra%20tasks%20to%20do%20while%20he%20kept%20working.%20For%20about%20two%20months%2C%20he%20was%20working%20his%20regular%20job%20and%20then%20on%20this%20extra%20work.%20Sometimes%2C%20it%20was%2016%20hours%2C%2018%20hours%20a%20day.%20Our%20lives%20stopped%20because%20he%20had%20so%20many%20things%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20very%20confident.%20And%20we'd%20keep%20talking%20about%20it.%20His%20goal%20was%20to%20finish%20at%20least%20a%20week%20in%20advance%20of%20the%20deadline%20so%20he%20could%20check%20whether%20more%20information%20was%20needed%20and%20make%20sure%20everything%20was%20OK.%20He%20did%20finish%20a%20week%20early.%20He%20was%20very%20confident%20about%20the%20job%20he%20did.%20He%20talked%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20peers%20about%20what%20he%20was%20doing.%20So%20he%20checked%20the%20work%20he%20had%20to%20do%20and%20felt%20he%20was%20OK.%20The%20weekend%20before%20it%20was%20due%2C%20we%20even%20took%20a%20trip.%20We%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20go%20to%20the%20ocean%20and%20enjoy%20it%20because%20everything%20is%20OK.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20presented%20what%20he'd%20done%2C%20he%20didn't%20pass.%20I%20was%20worried%20for%20him%3B%20we've%20been%20together%20almost%2020%20years%2C%20and%20I'd%20almost%20never%20seen%20him%20cry.%20It's%20been%20crushing%20to%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20fail%20because%20you%20didn't%20finish%20the%20job%2C%20you%20accept%20that.%20He%20had%20peers%20that%20didn't%20finish%20the%20tasks%2C%20but%20he%20did.%20The%20process%20was%20not%20fair.%20His%20boss%2C%20on%20the%20same%20day%20he%20received%20his%20grade%2C%20asked%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20kind%20of%20message%20do%20you%20want%20me%20to%20give%20your%20peers%20about%20your%20leaving%20the%20company%3F%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20not%20the%20moment%20to%20say%20that.%20The%20boss%20could%20have%20said%20there%20was%20an%20option%20to%20appeal%2C%20but%20he%20didn't.%20My%20husband%20had%20to%20figure%20that%20out%20on%20his%20own.%20His%20boss%20didn't%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20see%20where%20you%20failed%2C%20what%20you%20can%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20this%20process%20is%20not%20designed%20to%20improve%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20in%20his%20position.%20He%20showed%20me%20the%20good%20comments%20he%20received%20about%20his%20work%20from%20customers%20and%20peers.%20All%20of%20his%20colleagues%20were%20surprised%20that%20he%20was%20going%20through%20this%20process.%20So%20a%20lesson%20for%20them%20is%20if%20he%20can%20go%20through%20this%2C%20all%20of%20you%20can%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20like%20someone%20had%20died.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20give%20you%20five%20days%20to%20decide%20on%20whether%20to%20appeal.%20It%20was%20a%20really%20emotional%20moment%20for%20us.%20He%20wasn't%20trusting%20his%20own%20capabilities.%20He%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20go%20through%20the%20appeal.%20I%20need%20to%20know%20that%20I%20tried%20everything%20until%20the%20end%20because%20I%20know%20that%20I%20did%20a%20good%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20it%20was%20like%20someone%20had%20died.%20It%20was%20very%20hard%20for%20him%20to%20get%20confident%20again%20because%20he'd%20never%20been%20fired%20from%20any%20job.%20I%20would%20accept%20if%20this%20had%20happened%20to%20me%20because%20I%20complain%20a%20lot%20in%20my%20job%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20other%20places%20he%20worked%2C%20he%20was%20always%20the%20best%20employee.%20So%2C%20this%20was%20very%20difficult%20for%20him%20and%20for%20me%20to%20accept%20that%20he%20was%20going%20through%20this.%20He%20was%20classified%20as%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20employees%20even%20after%20receiving%20praise%20and%20compliments%20from%20customers%20and%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20appeal%2C%20there%20was%20a%20person%20from%20human%20resources%20who%20provided%20him%20with%20the%20final%20decision.%20She%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSorry.%20I%20saw%20your%20document%20and%20how%20much%20you%20tried%2C%20blah%2C%20blah%2C%20blah.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20as%20well.%20It%20was%20very%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20keep%20focused%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0not%20just%20thinking%20about%20the%20future%2C%20but%20thinking%20about%20his%20feelings.%20My%20husband%20even%20lost%20a%20lot%20of%20weight%20during%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20income%20is%20much%20higher%20than%20mine.%20So%20we%20tried%20to%20think%20about%20what%20we%20would%20do.%20We%20have%20a%20child.%20I%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20calculations%20about%20how%20many%20months%20we%20could%20go%20without%20my%20husband's%20job.%20Luckily%2C%20he%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20interviewing%20for%20other%20roles%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20husband%20is%20a%20role%20model%20for%20our%20child.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20confident%20it%20was%20the%20right%20decision%20to%20keep%20going%20until%20the%20final%20stage%20of%20this%20process%2C%20even%20though%20we%20discovered%20that%20maybe%20it's%20not%20really%20designed%20to%20improve%20the%20performance%20of%20someone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20had%20decided%20to%20leave%20earlier%2C%20he%20might%20be%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20still%20be%20there.%26quot%3B%20We%20now%20see%20the%20decision%20is%20not%20based%20on%20the%20work%20you've%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20was%20a%20role%20model%20for%20our%20child%20in%20part%20because%20of%20Amazon.%20So%20it's%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20has%20the%20cool%20job%3B%20mom%20has%20the%20regular%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20child%20saw%20my%20husband's%20situation%20%E2%80%94%20his%20mood%2C%20his%20face%2C%20how%20sad%20he%20was%2C%20the%20crying%20%E2%80%94%20we%20had%20to%20explain.%20My%20husband%20said%20that%20he%20had%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20for%20his%20job.%20So%2C%20there%20were%20weekends%20that%20he%20was%20not%20able%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20been%20planning%20a%20trip%20for%20this%20year.%20We%20told%20our%20child%20this%20trip%20was%20no%20longer%20on%20the%20table.%20That%20led%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20crying%20%E2%80%94%20not%20because%20of%20the%20trip%20but%20because%20it's%20very%20hard%20for%20a%20kid%20to%20see%20their%20hero%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20shirts%20with%20Amazon%20on%20them.%20Our%20child%20saw%20him%20wearing%20one%20recently%20and%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20are%20you%20wearing%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMargaret%20Callahan%2C%20an%20Amazon%20spokesperson%2C%20told%20BI%20via%20email%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BLike%20most%20companies%2C%20we%20have%20a%20performance%20management%20process%20that%20helps%20our%20managers%20identify%20who%20on%20their%20teams%20are%20performing%20well%20and%20who%20may%20need%20more%20support.%20For%20the%20small%20number%20of%20employees%20who%20are%20underperforming%2C%20we%20use%20performance%20management%20programs%20to%20help%20them%20improve%2C%20and%20many%20employees%20do%20just%20that.%20Sometimes%20the%20programs%20result%20in%20employees%20leaving%20the%20company.%20Business%20Insider%20declined%20to%20share%20the%20information%20needed%20to%20verify%20this%20individual's%20account%2C%20but%20from%20the%20questions%20we%20were%20asked%2C%20it's%20likely%20this%20essay%20will%20contain%20inaccuracies%20about%20our%20performance%20management%20process.%20Using%20an%20unverified%2C%20anonymous%20anecdote%20from%20one%20person%20to%20suggest%20their%20experience%20is%20representative%20of%20the%20experiences