f%20the%20applicant%20%5Bthe%20accused%5D%20with%20the%20victim%20%5Bthe%20complainant%5D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20ruled%2C%20citing%20evidence%2C%20that%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20withdrawal%20from%20his%20commitment%20to%20marriage%20due%20to%20his%20parents%E2%80%99%20disagreement%20with%20their%20union%20does%20not%20warrant%20charging%20him%20with%20the%20offence%20punishable%20under%20Section%20375%20(rape)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20had%20approached%20the%20high%20court%20for%20relief%20after%20a%20local%20sessions%20court%20rejected%20his%20application%20to%20be%20discharged%20from%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecutor%20argued%20that%20as%20per%20the%20FIR%2C%20the%20accused%20obtained%20the%20complainant%E2%80%99s%20consent%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20false%20promise%20of%20marriage%20and%20since%20inception%2C%20the%20applicant%20%5Bthe%20accused%5D%20had%20no%20intention%20to%20marry%20the%20victim%20%5Bthe%20complainant%5D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20since%20the%20accused%20obtained%20the%20complainant%E2%80%99s%20consent%20on%20false%20premises%2C%20Section%20375%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20rape%2C%20would%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20accused%20argued%20that%20he%20had%20offered%20to%20marry%20the%20complainant%20but%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20interested%20at%20all%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20bench%20comprising%20Justice%20M.W.%20Chandwani%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20appears%20from%20the%20WhatsApp%20chats%20between%20the%20applicant%20and%20the%20victim%20that%2C%20initially%20the%20applicant%20was%20ready%20to%20marry%20the%20victim%2C%20but%20it%20is%20the%20victim%2C%20who%20denied%20and%20informed%20the%20applicant%20that%20she%20will%20marry%20another%20boy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20only%20when%20the%20applicant%20got%20engaged%20with%20another%20gi