ticipating%20a%2077%25%20surge%20in%20new%20cancer%20cases%20to%20over%2035%20million%20by%202050%2C%20with%20deaths%20nearly%20doubling%20from%202012%20to%20exceed%2018%20million.%20Key%20factors%20contributing%20to%20this%20alarming%20trend%20included%20tobacco%20use%2C%20alcohol%20consumption%2C%20obesity%2C%20population%20aging%2C%20and%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20cancer%20before%20the%20age%20of%2075%20was%20calculated%20at%2010.6%25%2C%20while%20the%20risk%20of%20succumbing%20to%20cancer%20by%20the%20same%20age%20stood%20at%207.2%25.%20On%20a%20global%20scale%2C%20these%20risks%20were%20significantly%20higher%20at%2020%25%20and%209.6%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELung%20cancer%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20common%20cancer%2C%20accounting%20for%2012.4%25%20of%20new%20cases%20and%20nearly%2019%25%20of%20total%20cancer%20deaths.%20Breast%20cancer%20followed%20closely%20as%20the%20second%20most%20common%2C%20contributing%20to%2011.6%25%20of%20total%20new%20cases%20and%207%25%20of%20global%20cancer%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECervical%20cancer%2C%20although%20the%20eighth%20most%20commonly%20occurring%20globally%2C%20ranked%20ninth%20in%20causing%20cancer-related%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20prevalence%2C%20the%20IARC%20expressed%20optimism%20about%20the%20potential%20elimination%20of%20cervical%20cancer%20as%20a%20public%20health%20problem%20through%20the%20WHO%20Cervical%20Cancer%20Elimination%20Initiative.%20This%20initiative%2C%20urging%20countries%20to%20maintain%20an%20incidence%20rate%20below%204%20per%201%20lakh%20women%2C%20emphasised%20key%20strategies%20such%20as%20HPV%20vaccination%2C%20regular%20screenings%2C%20and%20efficient%20treatment%20protocols.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20interim%20budget%2C%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20announced%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20push%20for%20cervical%20cancer%20vaccination%20for%20girls%20in%20the%20age%20group%20of