%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffake-news-online-hate-swell-indonesia-anti-rohingya-sentiment%2Famp_articleshow%2F107376366.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Ffake-news-online-hate-swell-indonesia-anti-rohingya-sentiment%2Famp_articleshow%2F107376366.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Requiem%20for%20Rashid%20Khan%3A%20The%20Finest%20'Khayal'%20Vocalist%20Knows%20No%20Language%20Other%20Than%20Music%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02182754%2FEffect-95.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20perpetually%20unhappy%2013-year-old.%20I%20was%20losing%20faith.%20I%20had%20somewhat%20discovered%20nihilistic%20writers%2C%20but%20I%20also%20loved%20Marx.%20And%20I%20romanticized%20a%20country%20that%20no%20longer%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20we%20were%20never%20formally%20introduced%20to%20music.%20With%20the%20exception%20of%20a%20mini%20Casio%20keyboard%20that%20my%20father%20gifted%20me%20when%20I%20was%20quite%20young%2C%20I%20have%20no%20childhood%20musical%20memories.%20The%20keyboard%20had%20pre-recorded%20melodies%20in%20its%20%E2%80%9CSong%20Bank%E2%80%9D.%20While%20randomly%20listening%20to%20them%20%E2%80%94%20as%20I%20cheerfully%20pretended%20to%20play%20the%20keys%20%E2%80%94%20I%20always%20wondered%20why%20would%20certain%20melodies%20sadden%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESadness%2C%20in%20our%20home%2C%20was%20always%20tied%20to%20words.%20How%20could%20something%20wordless%2C%20after%20all%2C%20make%20me%20feel%20sad%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20no%20one%20liked%20music%20at%20home.%20There%20were%2C%20of%20course%2C%20old%20Bollywood%20and%20Pakistani%20songs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20ghazals%20by%20iconic%20artists%2C%20to%20a%20certain%20extent.%20However%2C%20the%20latter%20were%20always%20appreciated%20solely%20for%20their%20lyrical%20material.%20Ghazal%20singers%20were%20often%20judged%20whenever%20they%20mispronounced%20any%20Urdu%20words.%20All%20the%20praise%20belonged%20to%20the%20poets%20alone.%20I%20remember%20once%20my%20mother%20politely%2C%20and%20rightly%2C%20told%20me%20it%20was%20really%20embarrassing%20not%20to%20remember%20the%20words%20accurately%20while%20quoting%20a%20poet.%20I%20must%20have%20forgotten%20a%20couplet%20while%20reciting%20it%20at%20a%20family%20gathering.%20In%20the%20Quranic%20tradition%2C%20the%20universe%20came%20into%20being%20after%20God%20commanded%20a%20singe%20word%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EKun%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Be.%E2%80%9D%20In%20our%20home%2C%20no%20medium%20was%20as%20considered%20as%20sacred%20as%20text%20and%20no%20other%20art%20form%20could%20be%20taken%20as%20seriously%20as%20poetry.%20However%2C%20this%20was%20about%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20early%20morning%20in%202002%20%E2%80%94%20when%20I%20was%2013%20%E2%80%94%20I%20met%20something%20new.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20a%20new%20language%20opened%20her%20warm%20embrace%20for%20me.%20She%20carried%20an%20unknown%20melancholia%2C%20intertwined%20with%20an%20otherworldly%20pleasure.%20I%20heard%20a%20random%20old%20Hindi%20song%20on%20TV.%20The%20song%20deeply%20saddened%20me%2C%20as%20if%20it%20had%20broken%20something%20inside%20me.%20The%20haunting%20sadness%20was%20not%20linked%20to%20the%20song%E2%80%99s%20lyrics.%20By%20this%20time%2C%20thanks%20to%20my%20childhood%20friend%2C%20the%20little%20Casio%20keyboard%2C%20I%20had%20taught%20myself%20to%20play%20song%20tunes%20to%20some%20extent.%20Even%20though%20I%20had%20just%20heard%20that%20song%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20it%20deeply%20resonated%20with%20me%2C%20and%20its%20essence%20and%20the%20basic%20melody%20of%20the%20mukhra%20had%20remained%20in%20my%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20way%20to%20find%20it.%20The%20internet%20was%20slowly%20creeping%20in%20but%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20access%20to%20it%20all%20the%20time.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20there%20was%20no%20YouTube.%20How%20could%20one%20find%20a%20song%20then%20if%20one%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20remember%20the%20lyrics%3F%20At%20the%20music%20society%20of%20our%20school%2C%20I%20went%20to%20meet%20the%20instructor.%20When%20I%20hummed%20the%20melody%20and%20tried%20to%20play%20the%20notes%20on%20the%20keyboard%20there%2C%20the%20instructor%20smiled%20and%20uttered%20two%20words%20I%20did%20not%20understand%3A%20%E2%80%9CPuriya%20Dhanashree%E2%80%9D.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20that%20meant.%20He%20told%20me%20it%20was%20the%20name%20of%20an%20evening%20raga%2C%20belonging%20to%20the%20Purvi%20that%2C%20and%20the%20song%20had%20been%20composed%20in%20that%20raga.%20None%20of%20that%20made%20much%20sense%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20words%20%E2%80%9CPuriya%20Dhanashree%E2%80%9D%2C%20however%2C%20I%20memorized.%20Or%20did%20I%20note%20them%20down%3F%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20recall%20now.%20But%20there%20was%20something%20about%20that%20melody%2C%20something%20about%20these%20strange%20sounding%20words%2C%20and%20something%20about%20that%20morning%2C%20which%20left%20me%20in%20a%20dreamlike%20valley%20with%20an%20everlasting%20evening.%20I%20had%20found%20the%20song.%20But%20the%20mystery%2C%20I%20was%20told%2C%20had%20a%20deeper%2C%20an%20older%20source.%20I%20could%20not%20wait%20to%20explore%20this%20new%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20quench%20my%20thirst%20for%20what%20I%20had%20recently%20discovered%2C%20I%20checked%20a%20few%20of%20Lahore%E2%80%99s%20music%20stores%20within%20my%20reach%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20transitioning%20from%20cassettes%20to%20CDs%20%E2%80%94%20but%20no%20one%20had%20any%20idea%20about%20what%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%20Everything%20was%20changing%20fast.%20It%20seemed%20everyone%20wanted%20to%20speed%20up%20to%20match%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20new%20millennium.%20Like%20any%20millennial%2C%20I%20had%20witnessed%20the%20transformation%20from%20audiocassettes%20to%20CDs%20and%20MP3